The change password function can be a problem if read/write access is allowed to an external LDAP that manages passwords for other applications aside from Confluence.  If a user changes their password for Confluence they have the potential of changing their password for a number of other applications which can cause confusion for an end user who does not know LDAP.  To alleviate this confusion, we would like to see a 'disable change password function' option in the administrative screens of Confluence.

