When using XML-RPC to set the user information, a conversion from wiki markup to the new storage format is performed.
The display of the user information however still relies on wiki markup and therefor shows HTML source instead of the intended rendering of the submitted wiki markup:
Inserting the same wiki markup straight into the profile editor site results in correct rendering. (Screenshots attached)

Sample client with Confluence.pm to reproduce problem:
{code}
#!/usr/bin/perl 

use strict;
use warnings;
use Confluence;

$Confluence::API = 'confluence2';

my $conf = Confluence->new('http://localhost:1990/confluence/rpc/xmlrpc', 'admin', 'admin');

my $info = $conf->getUserInformation('admin');
$info->{'content'} = '{{insert text here}}';
$conf->setUserInformation($info);
{code}

