According to Justin Koke (Atlassian) in CWD-2745:

{quote}Justin Koke [Atlassian] added a comment - 26/Mar/12 11:07 PM - edited

The specific issue is in Confluence, there is no specific AOP transaction interception over the mutation calls for the CrowdService. This cannot be fixed in Crowd. The CrowdService doesn't even know it is, or needs to be running in a transaction due to the fact that it is invoking an SPI, and the SPI implementation is what dictates if a transaction needs to be in play, and in this case it is the Hibernate 2 SPI implementation from Confluence that requires mutation calls to be run within a transaction..
{quote}

Would prefer not to have to wrap calls to Crowd API in transaction in Atlassian Confluence plugin code. See: https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CWD-2745

Thank you for your consideration in this matter. There is a workaround, but having to use transactions is poorly documented and not intuitive.

