This feature request is raised based on a support ticket:

{quote}
When a page is edited it is moved to the top of the Recently Updated List (suppose it is not currently at the top of the list). As currently implemented, the view change link compares the most recent version of this page (call it y) to the previous version of the page (call it z).

Now, suppose the next edit to any Confluence page is to this same page (so it is now at version x). As currently implemented, the view change link displays a comparison between x and y; it would be ideal for it to display a comparison between x and z.

*As long as this page stays in the top position in the Recently Edited feed, the view change links to the changes between the current version of the page and the version of the page before it was moved to the top position in the Recently Edited feed.*
{quote}

Essentially, this option would allow users to see more meaningful diffs when a single page is updated repeated within a short amount of time.

